verses.roman:
aneka karilā yatna, nā haya cetana
prabhure uṭhāñā ghare ānilā bhakta-gaṇa

synonyms: aneka—many; karilā—made; yatna—endeavors; nā haya—there was not; cetana—consciousness; prabhure—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; uṭhāñā—lifting; ghare—home; ānilā—brought; bhakta-gaṇa—the devotees.
translation: The devotees tried to rouse the Lord by various means, but His consciousness did not return. Therefore they all lifted Him and brought Him back home.
